node.accessibility_caption: Photo by James Lloyd Cole in New Forest, Hampshire. May be an image of the Cotswolds, tree and outdoors.

node.text: The New Forest would be a gorgeous place to live. Imagine seeing horses roaming free in the forest on a misty morning drive to work? I don’t know of anywhere else in England you get that!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by James Lloyd Cole in Brockenhurst, Hampshire. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: The road beyond this gatehouse really sparks your imagination. Where do you think it might lead? 🧚‍♂️ ✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by James Lloyd Cole on September 15, 2021. May be an image of tree, nature and the Cotswolds.

node.text:
“It looks like a painting” has never been more accurately used.
Entering this garden, you feel a sense of enchantment, like you’re in a different world almost. 🧚‍♂️

What do you like most about it? I’m obsessing over those windows!

Thanks to @whatstacydid for telling me about this gem.

node.text: Welcome to Stanton, a quaint village in the North Cotswolds, where you’re more likely to see a line of horses than a line of cars. I’ve never been here and not seen people on horseback.

node.text:
The house at the end of the street.
This is the famous Arlington Row, built at the end of the 14th century. The entire row is now grade I listed, meaning they’re of significant historical importance and cannot be tampered with.

node.text: Now that is a front garden to be proud of! The cute staircase, the climbing roses, it’s all too much 😍

node.text: Mermaid Street managed to look incredible, even on the most boring, dreary of mornings. Where is your favourite street in Britain?

node.text:
Is this the coolest shower you’ve ever seen? Surrounded by fairy lights, misty steam and fern leaves. 🌿
I’ve wanted to visit @mallinsonswoodlandretreat again ever since I was there in 2019. It‘s often booked, as it’s one of the most epic treehouses in Britain. It even has a 360 degree rotating fire in the centre & a hot tub on the roof. 😳

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by James Lloyd Cole on September 08, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: Welcome to Kiftsgate Gardens. There’s much to see! A gorgeous Manor House, rose borders, avenues of flowers. They even have a lower garden with an outdoor pool, overlooking the Cotswolds countryside. I particularly love the terrace, it’s the perfect place to take in the views over afternoon tea. 🫖
